The National Cereals and Produce Board stand at a past ASK Show in Eldoret [Peter Ochieng, Standard]  More than 80 exhibitors have confirmed participation in this year’s Eldoret Agricultural Society of Kenya (ASK) show.  Organisers of the trade fair, the first in ASK annual calendar, said they expect more than 100 exhibitors in the three-day event.  Branch chairperson Susan Seron said all was set for the fair to be staged at the showground on the Eldoret – Kisumu highway from March 2 to 5.  “The event presents a good forum for agricultural producers to interact with players in the industry on latest production skills and emerging trends that will enable farmers generate good returns on their investment,” she said. This year's theme is “Promoting innovation and technology in agriculture and trade."  By Stephen Rutto | 3 hours ago By Antony Gitonga | 3 hours ago By Kennedy Gachuhi | 3 hours ago By Lynn Kolongei | 3 hours ago